         <abstract>
            <p>A general procedure is described for treating a movable singularity in an integral. This enables us to change the original integral I&lt;sub&gt;0&lt;/sub&gt; into GI&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;, where G depends only on the parameters of the singularity and I&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; is a new integral which exists for all values of the parameters. The results are then applied to the particular problem of evaluating. ∫&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;-1&lt;/sub&gt; f(x)dx/{(1 - x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;)(1 - k&lt;sup&gt;2x&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;)}&lt;sup&gt;1/2&lt;/sup&gt;, where f is entire and k varies between 0 and 1. Some new quadrature schemes and new effective methods of evaluating incomplete elliptic integrals are derived.</p>
          </abstract>
